# Privacy Policy — Everything 2x

Last updated: May 5, 2026

Everything 2x is a Chrome extension developed by Victor Humenhuk. It sets video and audio elements to your chosen default playback speed.

## Summary

- No data leaves your browser.
- No tracking, analytics, ads, telemetry, or remote code.
- Settings are stored only in Chrome's extension storage.
- The extension does not sell, share, or transmit user data.

## What the extension does

Everything 2x applies your chosen playback speed to HTML5 `<video>` and `<audio>` elements on websites you visit. It runs content scripts on pages so it can detect media elements, apply the rate, and re-apply it when a site resets playback to 1.0x.

## Data collection

The extension does not collect, store, transmit, or share:

- Personal information
- Browsing history
- Web page content
- Account data
- Location data
- Analytics or telemetry
- Authentication, financial, or payment information

## Data storage

The extension stores only your settings:

- Enabled or disabled state
- Default playback speed

These settings are stored in `chrome.storage.sync` so Chrome can sync them across your signed-in Chrome browsers. If sync storage is unavailable, the extension falls back to local extension storage. Settings are not sent to Victor Humenhuk or to any third-party server by this extension.

## Network requests

Everything 2x does not make external network requests. All JavaScript is bundled with the extension. There is no remote code, analytics SDK, tracking pixel, or telemetry endpoint.

## Permissions

- `storage`: saves your chosen speed and enabled state.
- Host access (`<all_urls>`): lets the content script detect and control media elements on every site and iframe.

The extension does not request the `tabs` permission.

